# OpenTelemetry Node.js

The OpenTelemetry JavaScript SDK instruments Node.js processes. The most important rule is startup order: initialize the SDK before importing libraries you want to auto-instrument.

## Install

```bash
npm install @opentelemetry/api @opentelemetry/sdk-node @opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node @opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-http @opentelemetry/exporter-metrics-otlp-http @opentelemetry/sdk-metrics @opentelemetry/resources @opentelemetry/semantic-conventions
```

## Generate Bootstrap

```bash
node nodes/opentelemetry/nodejs/scripts/create-node-bootstrap.mjs --service-name checkout-api --service-version 1.7.3 --out instrumentation.mjs
OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:4318 node --import ./instrumentation.mjs ./server.js
```

The script creates an ESM bootstrap file using `NodeSDK`, `getNodeAutoInstrumentations`, OTLP/HTTP trace export, OTLP/HTTP metric export, resource attributes, and clean shutdown hooks.

## Manual Spans

```javascript
import { trace, SpanStatusCode } from '@opentelemetry/api';

const tracer = trace.getTracer('checkout-service', '1.7.3');

export async function chargeCard(payment) {
  return tracer.startActiveSpan('checkout.charge_card', async (span) => {
    try {
      span.setAttribute('payment.provider', payment.provider);
      span.setAttribute('checkout.amount_cents', payment.amountCents);
      const result = await provider.charge(payment);
      span.setAttribute('payment.approved', result.approved);
      return result;
    } catch (error) {
      span.recordException(error);
      span.setStatus({ code: SpanStatusCode.ERROR, message: error.message });
      throw error;
    } finally {
      span.end();
    }
  });
}
```

## Metrics

```javascript
import { metrics } from '@opentelemetry/api';

const meter = metrics.getMeter('checkout-service', '1.7.3');
const checkoutCounter = meter.createCounter('checkout.requests', {
  description: 'Checkout requests accepted by the service'
});

checkoutCounter.add(1, {
  'checkout.result': 'accepted',
  'deployment.environment.name': process.env.NODE_ENV || 'development'
});
```

Use [[opentelemetry/semantic-conventions]] before inventing attributes, and keep metric attributes low-cardinality.

## Environment

```bash
export OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=checkout-api
export OTEL_RESOURCE_ATTRIBUTES=service.version=1.7.3,deployment.environment.name=production
export OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://otel-collector:4318
export OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_PROTOCOL=http/protobuf
export OTEL_TRACES_SAMPLER=parentbased_traceidratio
export OTEL_TRACES_SAMPLER_ARG=0.10
```

Use [[opentelemetry/troubleshooting#sdk-startup]] if spans do not appear.
